speaker: Doctor
text: Ay, sir. There are a crew of wretched souls

speaker: Doctor
text: That stay his cure. Their malady convinces

speaker: Doctor
text: The great assay of art, but at his touch

speaker: Doctor
text: (Such sanctity hath heaven given his hand)

speaker: Doctor
text: They presently amend.

speaker: Doctor
text: I have two nights watched with you but can

speaker: Doctor
text: perceive no truth in your report. When was it she

speaker: Doctor
text: last walked?

speaker: Doctor
text: A great perturbation in nature, to receive at

speaker: Doctor
text: once the benefit of sleep and do the effects of

speaker: Doctor
text: watching. In this slumb’ry agitation, besides her

speaker: Doctor
text: walking and other actual performances, what at any

speaker: Doctor
text: time have you heard her say?

speaker: Doctor
text: You may to me, and ’tis most meet you

speaker: Doctor
text: should.

speaker: Doctor
text: How came she by that light?

speaker: Doctor
text: You see her eyes are open.

speaker: Doctor
text: What is it she does now? Look how she rubs

speaker: Doctor
text: her hands.

speaker: Doctor
text: Hark, she speaks. I will set down what comes

speaker: Doctor
text: from her, to satisfy my remembrance the more

speaker: Doctor
text: strongly.

speaker: Doctor
text: Do you mark that?

speaker: Doctor
text: Go to, go to. You have known what you should

speaker: Doctor
text: not.

speaker: Doctor
text: What a sigh is there! The heart is sorely

speaker: Doctor
text: charged.

speaker: Doctor
text: Well, well, well.

speaker: Doctor
text: This disease is beyond my practice. Yet I have

speaker: Doctor
text: known those which have walked in their sleep,

speaker: Doctor
text: who have died holily in their beds.

speaker: Doctor
text: Even so?

speaker: Doctor
text: Will she go now to bed?

speaker: Doctor
text: Foul whisp’rings are abroad. Unnatural deeds

speaker: Doctor
text: Do breed unnatural troubles. Infected minds

speaker: Doctor
text: To their deaf pillows will discharge their secrets.

speaker: Doctor
text: More needs she the divine than the physician.

speaker: Doctor
text: God, God forgive us all. Look after her.

speaker: Doctor
text: Remove from her the means of all annoyance

speaker: Doctor
text: And still keep eyes upon her. So, good night.

speaker: Doctor
text: My mind she has mated, and amazed my sight.

speaker: Doctor
text: I think but dare not speak.

speaker: Doctor
text: Not so sick, my lord,

speaker: Doctor
text: As she is troubled with thick-coming fancies

speaker: Doctor
text: That keep her from her rest.

speaker: Doctor
text: Therein the patient

speaker: Doctor
text: Must minister to himself.

speaker: Doctor
text: Ay, my good lord. Your royal preparation

speaker: Doctor
text: Makes us hear something.

speaker: Doctor
text: Were I from Dunsinane away and clear,

speaker: Doctor
text: Profit again should hardly draw me here.
